Voluntary.definition: proceeding from one's own free choice or consent rather than as the result of duress

1 a.definition: proceeding from one's own free choice or consent rather than as the result of duress, coercion, or deception [a statement]

sub_terms.b: not compelled by lawdone as a matter of choice or agreement [ arbitration]
sub_terms.c: made freely and with an understanding of the consequences [a plea of guilty]

3.definition: made without valuable consideration or for nominal consideration [a conveyance]
